<paragraph blockId="5.[130,777,917,2028]" box="[132,350,917,943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">LECTOTYPIFICATION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[130,777,917,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<bibRefCitation author="SUTTON D. A." box="[132,351,948,975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" refId="ref3511" refString="SUTTON D. A. 1988. - A Revision of the Tribe Antirrhineae. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 p." type="book" year="1988">Sutton (1988: 257)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the type as: “Type: 
<collectingCountry name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Morocco</collectingCountry>
: 
<emphasis box="[172,204,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Ga</emphasis>
; Demnate, Djebel Imiifry, 
<date box="[504,633,980,1007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1879-07-18">18 vii 1879</date>
, 
<emphasis box="[646,775,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Ibrahim s.n.</emphasis>
(iso. BM!)”. However, this is not an effective designation according to Art. 9.12 of the 
<emphasis box="[453,502,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">ICN</emphasis>
because this specimen at BM cannot be considered as part of the exsiccatum of the Société Dauphinoise cited in the protologue.In fact, 
<bibRefCitation author="COSSON E." pageId="5" pageNumber="34" refId="ref2919" refString="COSSON E. 1891. - Illustrationes Florae Atlanticae. Reipublicae typographeo, Parisiis. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 53506" type="book" year="1891">Cosson (1891: 84)</bibRefCitation>
, in the protologue, stated: “ 
<taxonomicName box="[552,710,1140,1167]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="demnatense">
<emphasis box="[552,569,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[583,710,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Demnatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Coss. in herb. – Exs. Soc. Dauph. 
<emphasis box="[457,502,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Mar</emphasis>
. 522 
<emphasis box="[572,601,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">bis</emphasis>
(sub 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A. fruticosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)”. A diagnosis, a complete description of the species is provided by Cosson (l.c.), as well as the provenance “In collibus calcareis apricis. – Mar. 
<emphasis box="[454,569,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Dj. Imiifry</emphasis>
in provincia 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Demnate</emphasis>
ad boreali-orientem urbis 
<emphasis box="[475,541,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<collectingCountry box="[475,541,1300,1325]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Maroc</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. Imperio Maroccano peculiare”. Moreover an excellent and detailed illustration was given (Tab. 152, showing two stems with leaves, flowers and fruits, and several flowers details; image available at https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/113581#page/53). The specimens cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="COSSON E." box="[405,569,1459,1485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" refId="ref2919" refString="COSSON E. 1891. - Illustrationes Florae Atlanticae. Reipublicae typographeo, Parisiis. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 53506" type="book" year="1891">Cosson (1891)</bibRefCitation>
in the protologue are 
<typeStatus box="[172,264,1491,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">syntypes</typeStatus>
according to the Art. 9.6 and Art. 40 Note 1 of ICN. Based on the Art. 9.12 of the ICN, this material has priority in the 
<typeStatus box="[294,393,1554,1580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[130,777,917,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[811,1457,215,529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041291305" collectingDate="1881-07-04" collectingDateMax="1881-07-04" collectingDateMin="1879-07-18" collectionCode="P" collectorName="There" country="Morocco" location="Maroc" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" specimenCode="P038882611" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
<collectorName box="[155,217,1586,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">There</collectorName>
is a specimen at 
<collectionCode box="[411,426,1587,1613]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
(
<specimenCode box="[445,588,1586,1612]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P038882611</specimenCode>
) which bears six stems, with leaves, flowers and fruits, and a printed label (“ 
<collectorName box="[151,235,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Société</collectorName>
dauphinoise, 1882. / Nº 522 bis. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">Anarrhinum fruticosum</taxonomicName>
/ 
<collectorName box="[274,332,1682,1708]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Desf.</collectorName>
fl. 
<collectorName box="[368,436,1682,1709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Atl. II</collectorName>
, p. 52, t. 142. – DC. 
<collectorName box="[676,771,1682,1709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Prodr. X</collectorName>
, 289. / 
<collectorName box="[200,353,1714,1740]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Djebel Imiifry</collectorName>
, province 
<collectorName box="[458,577,1714,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">de Demnat</collectorName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[589,665,1714,1740]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Maroc</collectingCountry>
). / 
<date pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">
<collectingDate pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">4 juillet 1881</collectingDate>
</date>
. / 
<collectorName box="[213,354,1746,1772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Leg. Ibrahim</collectorName>
, / 
<collectorName box="[378,414,1746,1772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Dr.</collectorName>
<collectionCode box="[419,439,1746,1772]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15670" name="Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">E</collectionCode>
. Cosson.”) (
<figureCitation box="[564,627,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[500,511,2008,2025]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,215,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-35@6.[218,1369,215,1954]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 2. — Lectotype of Anarrhinum demnatense Cosson (P038882611)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4555432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4555432/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041291304" collectingDate="1881-07-04" collectingDateMax="1881-07-04" collectingDateMin="1879-07-18" collectionCode="P" collectorName="There" country="Morocco" location="Maroc" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" specimenCode="P038882611" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
In addition, another specimen at 
<collectionCode box="[362,377,1778,1804]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
(
<specimenCode box="[397,525,1778,1804]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P03882610</specimenCode>
) was traced. 
<collectorName box="[674,777,1778,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Although</collectorName>
not identified as “Société dauphinoise, 1882/Nº 522 
<emphasis box="[730,757,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">bis</emphasis>
”, it belongs probably to this collection since it was collected in the same place by 
<collectorName box="[365,453,1873,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Ibrahim</collectorName>
on 
<date box="[497,627,1873,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">
<collectingDate box="[497,627,1873,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">4 July 1881</collectingDate>
</date>
, and likely to be a 
<typeStatus box="[185,271,1906,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">syntype</typeStatus>
.
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041291302" collectingDate="1881-07-04" collectingDateMax="1881-07-04" collectingDateMin="1879-07-18" collectionCode="P" collectorName="There" country="Morocco" location="Maroc" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" specimenCode="P038882611" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
<collectorName box="[282,319,1905,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">On</collectorName>
the other hand, 
<typeStatus box="[502,676,1905,1931]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">other specimens</typeStatus>
(see e.g., 
<collectionCode box="[133,148,1938,1964]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
[barcode 
<specimenCode box="[259,384,1937,1963]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P03882612</specimenCode>
] and 
<collectionCode box="[450,512,1938,1964]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">MPU</collectionCode>
[barcode 
<specimenCode box="[622,771,1937,1963]" collectionCode="MPU" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">MPU237886</specimenCode>
; image available at https://explore.recolnat.org/occurrence/ 
<uuid box="[132,607,2001,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">2314BEC16FA04046B07B81C98F8A9F8C</uuid>
]) were collected by 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:2A3D87CBD503FF84FF4C6C21FC35FDBF:A74B6006D503FF84FC816FE3FB8CFF5F" box="[841,1111,215,241]" country="Morocco" name="Ibrahim in Djebel Imiifry" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Ibrahim in Djebel Imiifry</location>
(Demnate), but on 
<date box="[1319,1454,215,241]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1879-07-18">
<collectingDate box="[1319,1454,215,241]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1879-07-18">18 July 1879</collectingDate>
</date>
(as the specimen at 
<collectionCode box="[1030,1072,248,274]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bristol Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">BM</collectionCode>
cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="SUTTON D. A." box="[1181,1335,246,273]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" refId="ref3511" refString="SUTTON D. A. 1988. - A Revision of the Tribe Antirrhineae. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 p." type="book" year="1988">Sutton [1988]</bibRefCitation>
as “type”), and not on 
<date box="[941,1068,279,305]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">
<collectingDate box="[941,1068,279,305]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" value="1881-07-04">4 July 1881</collectingDate>
</date>
as reported in the above mentioned 
<typeStatus box="[813,904,311,337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCode box="[920,1061,311,337]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P038882611</specimenCode>
and 
<specimenCode box="[1115,1242,311,337]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P03882610</specimenCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,215,529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041291303" collectionCode="P" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" specimenCode="P03888261" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
In conclusion, among the material above cited, I here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[939,1034,375,401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1312,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="demnatense">
<emphasis box="[1063,1312,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Anarrhinum demnatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the specimen 
<specimenCode box="[811,938,406,432]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="Herbarium">P03888261</specimenCode>
because it is the only sure specimen that can be identified as part of the exsiccatumof the Société Dauphinoise with number “ 
<emphasis box="[972,1049,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">522 bis</emphasis>
”, such as part of the original material (Art. 9.4 of 
<emphasis box="[942,990,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">ICN</emphasis>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
